					<description><![CDATA[<p>Tavo Secures New Capital for Ophthalmology Development Tavo Biotherapeutics has secured $17m in Series A financing to accelerate its pipeline. Investment continues to flow into the ophthalmology sector as firms</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tavo-biotherapeutics-secures-17-million-ophthalmology-development/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tavo Biotherapeutics Secures $17 Million to Advance Glaucoma and Retinal Disease Therapies</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Tavo Secures New Capital for Ophthalmology Development</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tavo Biotherapeutics has secured $17m in Series A financing to accelerate its pipeline. Investment continues to flow into the ophthalmology sector as firms discover new ways to treat illnesses which compromise eyesight in the long-term. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Pureos Bioventures led the round. Polaris Partners also took part in the funding round. Existing investor Tau Capital supported Tavo for another round of financing. Funding will enhance Tavo&#8217;s capability of developing treatments against glaucoma and retinal disease.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Funding will be used to advance its ongoing clinical development work and fund its pre-clinical research. More resources will also be allocated to increase research capacities prior to key development milestones.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tavo is developing therapies to treat unmet needs in ophthalmology.Its programmes aim to preserve vision and improve patient outcomes. The company believes new treatment approaches remain necessary despite existing therapies available across several eye disease categories.</span></p>
<h2><b>Funding Supports Advancement of Lead Programmes</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new investment arrives as Tavo progresses two core development programmes. Both candidates target conditions affecting millions of patients globally. TAV-001 is being developed as a potential disease-modifying treatment for glaucoma. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The therapy is administered topically. It uses a dual mechanism designed to address biological processes linked to inflammation and degeneration associated with the disease. The company expects TAV-001 to enter a Phase 2 clinical trial during the second half of 2026. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Progress into the next stage of development marks an important milestone for the programme. TAV-002 represents Tavo’s second major asset. The therapy is a bispecific antibody designed to target both VEGF and another protein involved in retinal disease pathways.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Researchers are evaluating the programme for several serious eye conditions. These include wet age-related macular degeneration. The therapy may also address dry age-related macular degeneration. Diabetes-related retinal diseases remain another important target area.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes these programmes could offer new treatment options for patients. Many existing therapies require frequent intervention. Improved approaches could help reduce disease progression and preserve vision over longer periods.</span></p>
<h2><b>Leadership Expansion Strengthens Clinical Strategy<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202188" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202188" class="size-full wp-image-202188" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-elem_26ub9YfaVl2fO98_69fkbw_aBb8T5XvQ7ed8QWWihlhnQ_cover.png" alt="Biotech leadership team visualised with digital network and clinical development elements" width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202188" class="wp-caption-text">Tavo strengthens leadership team to support clinical development and future growth. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In addition to the financing news, Tavo made a few key leadership appointments to support the future growth. The business also expanded its executives and board of directors to add experienced members that have broad experience in the field of </span><a href="https://www.britannica.com/technology/biotechnology" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">biotechnology</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Dr. Federico Grossi was appointed as the company&#8217;s new Chief Medical Officer.  Prior to Tavo, he brings nearly thirty years of experience in both the clinical diagnostics and biotechnology arenas. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Dr. Grossi previously served as the Chief Medical Officer of Apellis Pharmaceuticals and in this role helped the development of two drugs to market. He noted that clinical development expertise will play a critical role as programmes move into advanced stages.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also appointed Daniel Bradbury as Chairman of the Board. Bradbury has more than forty years of life sciences experience. He previously served as Chief Executive Officer of Amylin Pharmaceuticals.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Additional board appointments include Dominik Escher and Nil Gural. Both executives bring experience in company building, financing, and therapeutic development. Their expertise is expected to support Tavo during its next growth phase.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/gigascale-capital-raises-250-million-to-back-physical-economy-innovation/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Gigascale Capital Raises $250 Million to Back Physical Economy Innovation</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Growing Demand Drives Innovation in Eye Disease Treatment</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Demand forophthalmology therapieswill continue to increase worldwide, since ageing populations bring increased incidences of glaucomarelated and retinal diseases. Earlier diagnosis has resulted in a greater number of treated patients, and the WHO lists vision impairment as a significant global health issue. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The need for therapies which improve the lives of patients, while decreasing the lifelong costs associated with a disease, has generated increased investor interest in ophthalmology; particularly those that are innovating in the development of therapies for the management of chronic ocular diseases. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Across the whole health sector, companies that target wide patient populations and address a number of critical needs have always been of considerable interest to investors. Tavo&#8217;s programs tackle key ophthalmology unmet needs and are underpinned by a differentiating scientific basis, stated Pureos Bioventures. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investor cited this as the major reason why it has agreed to be part of this financing round. &#8220;Tavo has an excellent scientific platform and a clear clinical strategy. This, along with strong underlying biology, makes for a compelling investment.&#8221; stated Dominik Escher. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This financing will fund development activities throughout the next few years and take its key programs through to significant milestones. Management intends to continue to pursue its plans for development and the delivery of new treatment alternatives to patients who presently lack any treatment options. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series A financing is a significant step forward for the business and adds financial strength to its ability to develop its ophthalmology. Coupled with a recently appointed leadership, the financing has placed the company well for future development.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tavo-biotherapeutics-secures-17-million-ophthalmology-development/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tavo Biotherapeutics Secures $17 Million to Advance Glaucoma and Retinal Disease Therapies</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
