		<title>DriveNets Secures $410M Series D for AI Network Growth</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/drivenets-secures-410m-series-d-for-ai-network-growth/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 12:06:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=202158</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>DriveNets, well known as a global developer of large-scale, cloud-native networking solutions, has announced the closure of a huge $410 million Series D financing. This has brought its overall funding</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/drivenets-secures-410m-series-d-for-ai-network-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">DriveNets Secures $410M Series D for AI Network Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://drivenets.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">DriveNets</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, well known as a global developer of large-scale, cloud-native networking solutions, has announced the closure of a huge $410 million Series D </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/invisix-raises-e20m-to-advance-ai-chip-manufacturing/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. This has brought its overall funding to $1 billion and its post-money valuation to an equally staggering $8.5 billion. The investment round demonstrates a fierce appetite from investors for backend infrastructure that will enable multivendor AI clusters to reach their full processing potential.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was co-led by Bessemer Venture Partners and Atreides Management. AMD and Red Dot Capital also joined the round, as well as previous investors Pitango and D1 Capital Partners. Capital infusion comes at a very stable financial time for DriveNets; they have been cash flow positive since 2025, with the current commercial pipeline and project backlog totalling over $1 billion.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Network Bottleneck in AI Factories</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Though those initial phases of the generative AI boom centered largely around buying up graphics processing units (namely NVIDIA and AMD GPUs), the engineering problem has very quickly shifted to the network fabric that binds them together. In today&#8217;s AI data centres, the GPUs come together in large, cohesive &#8220;AI factories&#8221;. Thousands upon thousands of individual accelerators working together to train huge foundational models.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It also means these GPUs are a very costly idle asset problem when they are just waiting for data to come over existing traditional networks. With GPUs being huge capital investments, every fraction of a second of latency equates to a lot of money being lost for cloud providers and AI research labs.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202160" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202160" class="size-large wp-image-202160" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/DriveNets_Logo-1536x325-1-1024x217.jpg" alt="DriveNets Logo" width="1024" height="217" /><p id="caption-attachment-202160" class="wp-caption-text">Source: DriveNets</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This particular operational risk is addressed by DriveNets&#8217; Ethernet-based AI fabric. Unlike competitors who rely on dedicated, proprietary networking appliances, the DriveNets Network Cloud software allows operators to deploy high-performance networks with normal, off-the-shelf whitebox hardware. End-to-end software optimisation of transport protocol, network interface cards (NICs), and the cluster&#8217;s internal communication eradicates the classic data choke point and allows for concurrent maximization of GPU usage. This fundamental rethinking of how to process tokens renders the old economics irrelevant.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/invisix-raises-e20m-to-advance-ai-chip-manufacturing/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> Invisix Raises €20M to Advance AI Chip Manufacturing</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Rise of Heterogeneous AI Architectures</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A significant reason that this round drew in chipmakers such as AMD is the widespread transition of the semiconductor industry to heterogeneous AI architectures. As data center workloads gradually move from model training toward more routine model inference, hyperscalers are looking for alternatives to inflexible, single-vendor hardware stacks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A heterogeneous design employs various AI accelerators from different chip companies in one cluster. This design enables the data center to best use power and intake chip cost per million tokens by diverting instructions to the ideal chip. Nevertheless, clusters&#8217; integration with different vendor chips generates intense friction in networking.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">DriveNets claims to be the essential layer of &#8220;neutral plumbing&#8221; for this multi-vendor world. The platform has collaborated with leading chip manufacturers, such as AMD and Broadcom, to produce field-proven, open reference designs that are &#8220;virtually seamless&#8221;, even when the elements are all from different vendors.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Timing and Inventory Scaling</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company intends to use this $410M capital to grow its commercial inventory and get ready for a predicted boom in worldwide hardware deployments during 2026/2027. Within a global hardware supply chain that is often subject to hardware lead times and component shortages, having a cash war chest to lock down immediate components can be a major advantage.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/drivenets-secures-410m-series-d-for-ai-network-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">DriveNets Secures $410M Series D for AI Network Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
