					<description><![CDATA[<p>Startup medical device manufacturer Veritas Aortic Solutions has successfully attracted a $12 million seed funding investment. The firm raised funds to develop and clinically test its novel device, treating aortic</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/veritas-secures-12m-to-advance-non-surgical-aortic-care/" data-wpel-link="internal">Veritas Secures $12M to Advance Non-Surgical Aortic Care</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Startup medical device manufacturer </span><a href="https://www.veritasaortic.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Veritas Aortic Solutions</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has successfully attracted a $12 million seed </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/inherent-raises-50m-to-build-ai-native-science-platform/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">investment. </span>The firm raised funds to develop and clinically test its novel device, treating aortic disease non-invasively without open-heart surgery.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by the Cedars-Sinai Intellectual Property Company (CSIPCo), a financial investor of the well-known Cedars-Sinai Health System, and by several existing investors related to the medical device incubator in QB8 Medical Technologies. Many well-known industry executives in the area of medical technology, such as former Medtronic CoreValve executive Chad Martinson, will be on the Veritas board of directors to lead the company through the upcoming clinical stages.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Targeting the Most Critical Section of the Heart</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A variety of abnormalities can occur in the aortic root and ascending aorta. Unsurprisingly, many are among the highest-risk conditions encountered in modern-day cardiovascular practice. Atrial root repair has traditionally involved complex, high-mortality open-chest surgery with cardiopulmonary bypass, cardioplegia, manual sewing of stitches, lines of synthetic grafts and replacement valves. This can be physically demanding for even some of the more robust patients.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Established out of inQB8 Medical Technologies as a stand-alone company (since late 2025), Veritas Aortic Solutions seeks to substitute these innovative processes with a 100% catheter-based solution. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_202147" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202147" class="wp-image-202147" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Veritas_Aortic_Solutions_Logo.jpg" alt="Veritas Aortic Solutions Logo" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-202147" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Veritas Aortic Solutions</p></div>
<p>The TVARC system unifies three components: a bioprosthetic aortic valve, an ascending aortic graft, and proprietary coronary perfusion ports called Chameleon Eyes. Surgeons deliver the device through a specialised transfemoral catheter system via a small groin incision. Once deployed, the device isolates and seals the diseased ascending aortic arch segment and restores healthy perfusion to the coronaries.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/inherent-raises-50m-to-build-ai-native-science-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Inherent Raises $50M to Build AI-Native Science Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">An Institutional and Strategic Backing</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While CSIPCo also adds money, it also signals their commitment as a specialised investment engine in health technologies that go to the heart of the clinical mission of the Cedars-Sinai Health System. The fact that the CEDARS environment attracts active investment suggests a significant clinical appetite for endovascular solutions to the treatment of the upper segments of the aortic system.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The framers of Veritas are also quite experienced in the structural heart field. Veritas is the 4th major program to result from the inQB8 incubator, a start-up portal founded by cardiac surgeon Arshad Quadri and device entrepreneur J. Brent Ratz. A few previous spinouts from the same team include CardiAQ Valve Technologies (transcatheter mitral valve replacement leader, acquired by Edwards Lifesciences) and MonarQ (tricuspid valve replacement leader, acquired by Peijia Medical).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Next Steps: Clinical Translation</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The availability of the $12 million in new seed funding has prompted Veritas to refocus its current activities on the commencement of human clinical trials from the preclinical validation process. Veritas plans to use the development funds to bolster its regulatory manufacturing capacity and leverage this to demonstrate the data in line with humanity&#8217;s clinical trials.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">If successfully implemented in further trials, the TVARC system may bring treatment for thousands of high-risk structural heart patients currently considered unsuitable for traditional open surgical therapy.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/veritas-secures-12m-to-advance-non-surgical-aortic-care/" data-wpel-link="internal">Veritas Secures $12M to Advance Non-Surgical Aortic Care</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
