		<title>Inherent Raises $50M to Build AI-Native Science Platform</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/inherent-raises-50m-to-build-ai-native-science-platform/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2026 15:23:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=202127</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Inherent has raised a $50 million seed round to fund the development of &#8220;Faraday&#8221;, an ambitious AI platform engineered to redefine the scientific method for the machine learning age completely.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/inherent-raises-50m-to-build-ai-native-science-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Inherent Raises $50M to Build AI-Native Science Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://inherentlabs.ai/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Inherent </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised a $50 million seed </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/xcena-raises-135m-series-b-for-memory-centric-computing/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">to fund the development of &#8220;Faraday&#8221;, an ambitious AI platform engineered to redefine the scientific method for the machine learning age completely.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The mega-seed round was jointly led by two of the giants of venture capital, Index Ventures and Radical Ventures, and was sprinkled with participation from NVIDIA&#8217;s V.C. wing, Nventurers. The underwriter list also includes an ensemble cast of deep tech and early-stage funds: Ex/Ante, Metaplanet, Macroscopic Ventures and Mythos Ventures.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Rewriting a 400-Year-Old Paradigm</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rather than building software designed to slide into existing laboratory or research workflows, Inherent&#8217;s explicit mission is to rethink the scientific method from first principles. The startup is focused on what they call &#8220;AI-native science&#8221;.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The lab is working on Faraday, a dedicated AI system designed not to do existing tasks more quickly but to generate new ones: to identify questions people didn&#8217;t think to ask in the first place. Faraday&#8217;s architecture connects human experts to semi-autonomous agents that self-enhance and can independently traverse hypothesis spaces that would take human minds hundreds of years to assemble.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202132" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202132" class="size-large wp-image-202132" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/AI-1024x853.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="853" /><p id="caption-attachment-202132" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Most AI systems today are fundamentally designed to answer questions,&#8221; said Danny Rimer, Partner at Index Ventures, in a statement accompanying the launch. &#8220;What they cannot do yet is exhibit the open-ended curiosity that produced historic, accidental breakthroughs like penicillin, the microwave, or even the GPU. That is the exact gap Inherent is building.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/xcena-raises-135m-series-b-for-memory-centric-computing/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">XCENA Raises $135M Series B for Memory-Centric Computing</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Pedigree of Frontier Research and White House Policy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Inherent’s massive valuation at the seed stage is heavily driven by its formidable founding team, which blends elite technical expertise with deep regulatory insight. The startup was founded by DeepMind alumni Tantum Collins, Edward Hughes, and Louis Kirsch, alongside Kaloyan Aleksiev, a veteran infrastructure engineer who joins from Reka AI and Microsoft.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While at DeepMind, Collins and Hughes worked closely on cooperative AI, a subfield of machine learning dedicated to improving collaboration between multiple AI systems and humans. Beyond his technical credentials, Collins brings rare geopolitical and policy experience to a frontier tech lab, having previously served as an AI policy advisor at the Biden White House.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The team&#8217;s positioning is further strengthened by the addition of Matt Clifford, co-founder of Entrepreneur First and the UK government&#8217;s former AI tsar, who has joined Inherent as a formal strategic advisor. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This dual strength in cutting-edge research and state-level policy positions Inherent uniquely to navigate both academic institutions and the massive government bodies that fund basic scientific discovery.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Public Benefit Structure as a Strategy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In an unusual move for a heavily venture-backed frontier AI lab, Inherent has launched as a Public Benefit Corporation (PBC). This legal framework requires the company&#8217;s executive board to balance shareholder returns with its stated public benefit charter, prioritising safety, transparency, and ethical scientific advancement.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Venture capitalists involved in the round frame this corporate structure as a competitive advantage rather than a regulatory constraint. In a blog post announcing the investment, Index Ventures noted:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;AI-native science will look and feel totally different to the scientific method we&#8217;ve grown used to over the past 400 years: it will be messier, less legible, but capable of exceptional outcomes. The lab of the future will be completely alien to us today.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By building governance metrics directly into its corporate DNA from day one, Inherent hopes to establish the ultimate baseline of trust required to deploy highly autonomous, self-improving agents into sensitive real-world fields like biochemistry, materials science, and advanced physics. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $50 million runway gives the London lab the necessary time to move Faraday from a theoretical framework to peer-reviewed breakthrough validation.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/inherent-raises-50m-to-build-ai-native-science-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Inherent Raises $50M to Build AI-Native Science Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
